AGI - It would have gone up to at least 50 dead and dozens of wounded the Israeli raid on the refugee camp in the north-west at Rafah>, in the Tal district to the Sultan, according to Hamas, which governs the Gaza Strip. "Israeli occupation committed a terrible massacre by bombing intensely and intentionally the center for displaced UNRWA Barkasat to the northwest of the Rafah Governorate," said the Hamas government office in a note. According to the authorities of the Strip, most victims are women and children.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Israeli army confirmed the Sunday evening attack on Rafah, and pointed out that it targeted a Hamas> headquarters while a high-level meeting of the terrorist group was underway. "The attack was carried out against terrorists, who are a target in accordance with international law, using precision ammunition and on the basis of intelligence information indicating the use of the area by Hamas terrorists," said the IDF in a note. The army states that the attack would cause a fire that spread in a field for Palestinian displaced persons, causing victims among civilians.
&nbsp;
According to the armed forces of the Jewish State, two high Islamist officials were killed during the operation: Yassin Rabia, head of Hamas operations in the West Bank, and Khaled Nagar, a member of the Hamas wing in the West Bank. The attack was carried out in the northwest of Rafah "on the basis of precise intelligence information", reads in the communiqué, "following the attack and the resulting fire several people would have been affected; the accident is being examined." A U.S. National Security Council spokesman reported that the White House is collecting information about what happened.
<div </div
The Israeli attack was also denounced by the Palestinian Red Crescent. "Our ambulances carry a large number of martyrs and wounded following the attack by the occupant on the tents of displaced persons near the UN headquarters, north west of Rafah," said the health organization on X, recalling that "this place had been indicated by Israeli occupation as a humanitarian zone". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Presidency of the Palestinian National Authority > believes that Israel has committed a "atroce massacre" >e launched&nbsp;a challenge to all resolutions of international legitimacy". The Anp then accused the Israeli forces of " deliberately targeting" the tents of the displaced.&nbsp;"In the light of the horrible Zionist massacre committed this evening by the criminal army of occupation against the tents of the displaced we invite the masses of our people in the West Bank, in Jerusalem, in the occupied territories and abroad to rise and march with rage against the massacre.
<h2>Borrell: relaunch of the EU mission
"I will put on the table a proposal to relaunch our Eubam Rafah mission on the civil system of borders, if it will be useful", announced the High Representative of the EU for Foreign Policy, Josep Borrell>, upon his arrival to the Foreign Council. "We were asked to do it. If we can, we will. But considering that everything must go in the direction of making the Palestinian Authority take responsibility on Gaza," he said. "Today the political free path is awaited, then there will be technical work to be done," said Borrell.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"We must respect the work of the International Criminal Court. We must respect the work of this institution and let the tribunal, without intimidation, decide what it thinks of this initiative of the public ministry. Unfortunately, it's not. The prosecutor and the court were strongly intimidated and accused of anti-Semitism. As always happens for anyone who does something that does not like the Netanyahu government," said the EU High Representative for Foreign Policy.
&nbsp;
"I think that the prosecution of anti-Semitism against the prosecutor of the International Criminal Court is totally unacceptable. Defining the anti-Semitic Court is too heavy. It's too important to use it on these occasions," he said. "And then there is the most important and even more important thing is the judgment of the International Court of Justice, which is the hub of international justice to act above the national level, is at the heart of the United Nations Charter. And here too we must express not only respect, but call for the implementation of the Court's decision. And now, unfortunately, what we have seen in the immediate hours is that Israel continues the military action that had been asked to stop. It also applies to Hamas who launches rockets against Israel. So both parties do not respect the Court's ruling," he added.
<h2> Spain, Ireland and Norway will recognise the State of Palestine
&nbsp;"Today our three countries, Ireland, Norway and Spain, will live a historical day that will surely approach the goal we all want: to achieve peaceful and secure coexistence in the Middle East," said Spanish Foreign Minister Manuel Albares, announcing the official recognition of the State of Palestine.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Albares then condemned a video published by his Israeli counterpart Israel Katz entitled "Hamas: Grazie Spagna" in which images of the Spanish flag and flamenco dancers are combined with spezzoni of the atrocities made by Hamas militiamen on October 7.
&nbsp;
"We will not fall into provocations. The video is scandalous and execrable," said Albares, stressing that "it is scandalous because the whole world knows, including my colleague in Israel, that Spain has condemned Hamas' actions since the first moment. It is execrable for the use of one of these symbols of Spanish culture."

