AGI - At least 11 people were killed and 50 wounds, three severely or severely >, in a Russian attack against a DIY hypermarket in Kharkiv, the second city of Ukraine, where "more than 200 people" could be at the time of impact, according to Kiev. According to the regional governor, Oleg Synegoubov, the Russian attack was carried out with two guided air bombs and at least 16 people would still be under the rubble.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The images published on Ukrainian social networks show the building with the cut roof and a huge column of black smoke coming out, while the firefighters turn off the flames triggered by the attacks with the water. According to the authorities, 10,000 square meters of structure were burned, but the firefighters are trying to report the situation under control. The Epitsentr hypermarket chain sells household appliances and DIY products.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky: "A brutal blow"</h2>
"Russia has inflicted another brutal blow to our city of Kharkiv - a building hypermarket -, in the middle of the day", denounced President Volodymyr Zelensky on Telegram. "At the moment we know that more than 200 people could have been inside the hypermarket. All services are already in place to help save people and turn off the fire," he added, condemning an attack in the middle of the day to a 'clearly civil' goal. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"A large number of people are missing. Many people are wounded," said Mayor Igor Terekhov, denouncing the attack as 'pure and simple terrorism'. According to the mayor, 15 store employees were not tracked and about 200 people were in the building at the time of the attack. "Only fools like Putin are able to kill and terrorize people in such a despicable way," said Zelensky, attacking the Russian president who ordered his troops to attack Ukraine in February 2022.
<h2>Bombardato il villaggio di Oktyabrsky, due morti</h2>
Two more people were killed and ten more wounds in the bombardment of Oktyabrsky village in the Russian region of Belgorod, bordering Ukraine. Governor Vyacheslav Gladkov reported on his Telegram channel. "The Ukrainian armed forces shot multiple MLRS rocket launchers on the village of Oktyabrsky, Belgorod district, with our great pain, two people died: a man and a woman had multiple injuries from splinters incompatible with life," the governor wrote. Among the ten wounded civilians, it is also an eight-year-old child.
&nbsp;
The Ukrainian president again invited Western allies to provide the country with more air defense systems. "If Ukraine had enough air defense systems and modern combat aircraft, these Russian attacks would be impossible," he said. "Every day we appeal to the world: give us air defense, save people."
&nbsp;
The city of Kharkiv, which before the war had a population of 1.5 million inhabitants and is located near the Russian border in the north-east of Ukraine, is regularly targeted by the forces of Moscow, which on May 10 also launched an offensive of land in the region. This offensive allowed them to conquer several cities and force Kiev to send reinforcements to the area. However, on Friday, Ukraine assured that the assault was "feeled".
&nbsp;
<h2>Medvedev: "A US attack would mean World War III"</h2>
&nbsp; Poland must understand that an American attack against Russian goals would mean the beginning of a world war. It is the new warning launched by Russian Security Council Vice-President Dmitri Medvedev on social.<br> Medvedev responded to the words of Polish Foreign Minister Radoslaw Sikorski, who in an interview with the Guardian said that the United States threatened Moscow to " annihilate" the Russian contingent in Ukraine if Moscow' on the field the nuclear weapon.<br> "First, the Yankees have not yet said anything like that, because they are more cautious than Poles. Secondly, an American attack on our objectives would mean the beginning of a world war, and any foreign minister, including a country like Poland, must understand it," warned Medvedev. " Thirdly, since another Polish President Duda recently announced his wish to deploy tactical nuclear weapons in Poland, Warsaw will not remain on the side and will surely receive his share of radioactive ashes," Medvedev wrote on X.

