In the course of the interview, we read again in the note of the Farnesina, Tajani announced that, after the first two packages of aid of 20 million already allocated, the Government decided to prepare a new, third package that, from the 20 million already decided in the past weeks, is willing to increase to 30 million euros. The "Food for Gaza" initiative, which the Vice President of the Council had presented to the Israeli Foreign Minister Katz during his visit to Rome on 7 April, was activated in coordination with FAO, PAM and FICROSS to bring concrete aid, in terms of food security, to the Palestinian population. It is a further support that is added to the work done by Italy on the humanitarian front during the past few months to exfiltrate from the Gaza Strip 156 Palestinian citizens, including 58 injured minors who benefited in Italy from the care of our hospitals and related escorts. In parallel, collaboration with the UAE from a medical point of view with the sending of Italian personnel in the United Arab Emirates, where our doctors helped to visit and operate some pediatric patients with severe traumas, transported from Gaza.
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
"We believe that it is necessary to work on the solution "two peoples, two states" in the framework of a broader political process that leads to peace, the result of a coordinated regional action, with a strong support from the international community. It is essential to address both the humanitarian emergency of the Palestinian people and its legitimate aspirations to have its own state and the legitimate security needs of Israel. The creation of a Palestinian State must be an integral part of this path," said the Minister and Deputy Prime Minister. Tajani reiterated that Italy will continue to ensure, as in the past, full support for the Palestinian Authority and its strengthening, as demonstrated by initiatives for the development of autonomous capacities in the field of governance and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> The meeting with Meloni</h2>
It was then the turn of the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni to meet Mustafa. The premier - informs a note of Palazzo Chigi - reiterated the Italian support for all efforts in place for a ceasefire, the release of all hostages in the hands of Hamas and a qualitative leap in humanitarian assistance to the people of Gaza. In the latter regard, it has been emphasized - it is added - the strong Italian commitment to the civilian population of Gaza also through further financing for the initiative 'Food for Gaza'.&nbsp;&nbsp; During the interview Meloni reiterated the need to restart a political process that leads to lasting peace based on the solution of the two States.
